# SFTP/FTP credentials
.vscode/sftp.json
**/.htpasswd

# Claude Code local settings (machine-specific, not for sharing)
.claude/settings.local.json

# Generic credential file patterns (defense in depth)
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
id_rsa*
**/sftp.json
**/*credentials*
**/*secrets*

# OS/editor junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Local notes (not for public repo)
CLAUDE.md
ARCHITECTURE.md
DESIGN.md
SEO.md
COMPONENTS.md
CHANGELOG.md
DEVELOPMENT_RULES.md
DEPLOY_CHECKLIST.md
IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md

# Root-level/scratch markdown stays untracked by default (mirrors the
# .vscode/sftp.json ignore list's *.md / README* coverage for publish
# prevention; that list already protects docs/ and tests/ independently,
# so this section governs Git tracking only, not publishing).
# docs/ is explicitly re-included below: it holds versioned engineering
# specs (engine-template.md, sansei-engine-design.md, docs/love/*) that
# engine-template.md treats as formal, diffable deliverables.
*.md
README*
!docs/**

# Dev-only test/tooling assets (Golden Master scripts, fixtures, Coverage/
# Snapshot). Tracked in Git: engine-template.md treats these as formal
# deliverables that must be diffable across changes; keeping them out of
# Git defeats the purpose of a Golden Master.
